name: Specialty Jams
description:
These are the flavors for our foodie fans. Not your everyday jam and toast situation over here!

Blueberry, Lavender, and Lemon is made with no added sugar - just local honey from Bluebonnet Bee Farm in Jacksonville, organic hand-ground lavender, fresh lemon zest + juice, and plump juicy blueberries.

Strawberry, Balsamic, Black Pepper is a must-have for your next level charcuterie boards (don’t do a family gathering without them!)

Blueberry compote is fantastic warmed and served over pancakes or waffles. It will also blow your mind as an addition to a blue cheese + bacon burger!

Raspberry & Basil is earthy and less tart than traditional raspberry jam. We love it with our croissants.

Fig and Honey jam blends perfectly ripe Brown Turkey figs (grown in Bullard) which we sweeten with Elzner Farms honey from Jacksonville, TX (no added sugar), and added a little lemon zest for brightness. We recommend pairing this jam with a shmear of gorgonzola on a crispy toast point and O.M.G. It will light up those taste buds! We also love this with cured meats and Marcona almonds.

This food is made in a home kitchen and is not inspected by the Department of state health services or a local health department.

name: Pasture Raised Whole Chicken
description:
Pasture raised, ethically produced, nutrient dense.

Each bird's foraging diet is supplemented with a soy-free, non-GMO chemical free feed, made right here in Texas. Each chicken will be sold as a whole bird (think of a beautiful roast chicken). All of our chickens are processed in a USDA inspected facility.

Why pasture raised? Pasture raised chicken is a healthier and tastier option for you and your family. Lower in saturated fats, higher in omega 3’s and vitamin A, it’s a smart choice to make for this reason alone. But when you add to it the superior flavor that comes from the chickens enjoying their days as nature intended (on grass foraging and hunting) PLUS the added benefit of knowing that you are actively supporting the soil regeneration here in East Texas by purchasing from Hood Family Farms - it’s really a no brainer.

name: Grass Fed Beef Short Ribs
description:
Pasture Raised Grass Fed Grass Finished beef, the most nutritious type of beef available. Dry aged 21 days for maximum flavor and tenderness. Short ribs are one of the most sought after cuts - tender and juicy and a lot of meat/rib.

Why Pasture Raised/Grass Fed? Grass fed beef is typically lower in fat. This provides a leaner, lower calorie, and easier to digest beef. Grass fed beef also has less mono-unsaturated fats, up to 5xs the Omega 3 fatty acids, significantly higher anti-oxidants, and about 300-500% as much Conjugated Linoleic Acid (studies have linked CLA to several health benefits including fat loss and increased resistance to things like heart disease, cancer and type 2 diabetes). Our cows are eating their natural diet and behaving in their natural way, roaming free on fresh pastures. Not only does this create a significant POSITIVE environmental impact, we believe this is also important for animal well being. Significant research has been done that shows animals with less stress hormones taste better.

description:

Why Pasture Raised/Grass Fed? Grass fed beef is typically lower in fat. This provides a leaner, lower calorie, and easier to digest beef. Grass fed beef also has less mono-unsaturated fats, up to 5xs the Omega 3 fatty acids, significantly higher anti-oxidants, and about 300-500% as much Conjugated Linoleic Acid (studies have linked CLA to several health benefits including fat loss and increased resistance to things like heart disease, cancer and type 2 diabetes). Our cows are eating their natural diet and behaving in their natural way, roaming free on fresh pastures. Not only does this create a significant POSITIVE environmental impact, we believe this is also important for animal well being. Significant research has been done that shows animals with less stress hormones taste better.
